<div id="review_626933230" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/626933230" />
    <a title="Peter Bringe" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8588820-peter-bringe"><img alt="Peter Bringe" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1333552758p2/8588820.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/626933230?book_show_action=true">May 28, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Peter Bringe" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Peter Bringe" href="/user/show/8588820-peter-bringe">Peter Bringe</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140440270" href="/book/show/446646.The_Imitation_of_Christ">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8588820-peter-bringe?shelf=applied-theology">applied-theology</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8588820-peter-bringe?shelf=culture">culture</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer626933230" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17762179495796768906">This book had some real good gems but the book as a whole was not as impressive. It is pretty good considering the time it was written (15th century), and makes some valuable points, but still has too much of an abandon-the-world mentality. <br/><br/>Some memorable quotes:<br/><br/>&quot;It is vanity to wish for long life, if you care little for a good life.&quot;<br/><br/>&quot;A wise lover values not so much the gift of the lover, as the love of the giver.&quot; </span>
  <span id="freeText17762179495796768906" style="display:none">This book had some real good gems but the book as a whole was not as impressive. It is pretty good considering the time it was written (15th century), and makes some valuable points, but still has too much of an abandon-the-world mentality. <br /><br />Some memorable quotes:<br /><br />"It is vanity to wish for long life, if you care little for a good life."<br /><br />"A wise lover values not so much the gift of the lover, as the love of the giver." </span>
  <a data-text-id="17762179495796768906" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


