<span id="freeTextContainer10264375043769515438"><b>First Read:</b> One of the most influential and spiritually inspiring books I have ever read. I didn&apos;t want it to end! I&apos;ll have to read it at least five more times to ingrain the wisdom into my forgetful mind. (2019)<br/><br/>------------------------------------<br/><br/><b>Second Read:</b> This book is a gold mine for the spiritual life. Thomas Ã  Kempis was greatly blessed by God with understanding and an awareness of the interior movings and inspirations of the human soul. No matter which stage one is on in their spiritual</span>
  <span id="freeText10264375043769515438" style="display:none"><b>First Read:</b> One of the most influential and spiritually inspiring books I have ever read. I didn't want it to end! I'll have to read it at least five more times to ingrain the wisdom into my forgetful mind. (2019)<br /><br />------------------------------------<br /><br /><b>Second Read:</b> This book is a gold mine for the spiritual life. Thomas Ã  Kempis was greatly blessed by God with understanding and an awareness of the interior movings and inspirations of the human soul. No matter which stage one is on in their spiritual journey, reading this book will be of exceptional benefit.<br /><br />Eventhough my first read-through took place a year ago, and proved informative and fruitful beyond anything I expected, the second read can be treated with no less regard for I am sure there were different passages that stood out and stirred my soul this time around. Afterall, life changes and so do we. For this reason I would do well to keep Imitation of Christ as my annual Lenten read. (2020)</span>
