<div id="review_633198838" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/633198838" />
    <a title="Alex Strohschein" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5940482-alex-strohschein"><img alt="Alex Strohschein" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1598513391p2/5940482.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/633198838?book_show_action=true">Jun 04, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alex Strohschein" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alex Strohschein" href="/user/show/5940482-alex-strohschein">Alex Strohschein</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780486431857" href="/book/show/220408.The_Imitation_of_Christ">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5940482-alex-strohschein?shelf=spiritual-classics">spiritual-classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5940482-alex-strohschein?shelf=devotionals">devotionals</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer633198838" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4994665844536828112">No wonder this book is such a spiritual classic! The writer offers some amazing insight and wisdom into the devotional life. One of the best chapters is &quot;The Different Motions of Nature and Grace&quot;. This book is itself subdivided into four books. The first three are solid, 5/5, but the last section, on Holy Communion, is what brings the overall rating down to a 4/5. As well, the books&apos; teachings are more ascetic than need be (though it increases its rhetorical power) &quot;For everything created by Go</span>
  <span id="freeText4994665844536828112" style="display:none">No wonder this book is such a spiritual classic! The writer offers some amazing insight and wisdom into the devotional life. One of the best chapters is "The Different Motions of Nature and Grace". This book is itself subdivided into four books. The first three are solid, 5/5, but the last section, on Holy Communion, is what brings the overall rating down to a 4/5. As well, the books' teachings are more ascetic than need be (though it increases its rhetorical power) "For everything created by God is good, and nothing is to be rejected if it is received with thanksgiving, for it is made holy by the word of God and prayer" (1 Tim. 4-4:5). The book is right to make us humble, to tell us to order our loves so that the Lord is our foremost, but at the same time, God created good and I believe He delights along with us when we have strawberries and cream.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4994665844536828112" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


